Prompt A (Medium A – Painting: Watercolor)
Create an artwork using watercolor painting that emphasizes the elements and principles of line, contrast, movement, texture, and unity. Use watercolor brushes, soft bristle brushes, watercolor paper, and diluted pigments to create a layered composition. Apply the wet-on-wet technique and gradient layering to allow colors to softly bleed and blend into each other. The artwork should feature a peaceful riverside landscape with trees bending in the wind, birds flying across the sky, and reflections moving in the water. Use flowing curved lines to create movement in the trees and water, while contrast between light sky and darker land areas creates emphasis. The watercolor should show transparency, soft edges, and natural color blending, creating a calm atmosphere. Texture should appear through watery gradients, subtle brush strokes, and layered washes of color that unify the entire scene.

Prompt B (Medium B – Printmaking: Linocut)
Create an artwork using the linocut printmaking process that emphasizes the elements and principles of line, contrast, movement, texture, and unity. Use linoleum carving tools, carving gouges, ink rollers (brayers), printing ink, and printing paper to produce the composition. The artwork should feature the same riverside landscape with trees bending in the wind, birds flying across the sky, and water reflections, but interpreted through bold carved lines and strong black-and-white contrast. Use carving techniques to cut away negative space, allowing the remaining raised areas to hold ink. Emphasize movement through curved carved lines in the trees and water, and create texture using repetitive carved marks. The design should rely on high contrast between inked surfaces and carved white areas to produce visual emphasis and unity. The final print should reflect the characteristic graphic boldness and expressive carved marks of linocut printmaking.
